{
  "info": {
    "name": "Loyalty Points App",
    "description": "JSON-RPC 2.0 API for the loyalty-points server. All methods are POSTed to the single /api endpoint. params MUST be a one-element array (the gorilla json2 codec unmarshals it into [1]interface{}).\n\nPreset credentials live in collection variables — {{email}}, {{password}}, {{name}}, {{accountName}} — and are shared by Register and Login, so editing them in one place keeps both in sync and you can log in with whatever you just registered. Public methods (Register, Login) need no token. Register and Login capture the returned {{token}}; Register also captures {{userID}} and {{accountID}} so protected calls (e.g. the wallet methods) reuse them automatically.\n\nTypical flow: run Register once, then Login (or any protected call) — variables are already populated.\n\nWallet.ProcessTransaction is callable by members on their own accounts. Wallet.ProcessTransactionBatch is admin-only: it applies an ordered batch sequentially in array order — a member token is rejected.\n\nImport into Requestly via Import -> Postman.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "http://localhost:8080",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "email",
      "value": "ada@example.com",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "password",
      "value": "hunter2pw",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "name",
      "value": "Ada Lovelace",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "accountName",
      "value": "Primary Wallet",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "token",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "userID",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "accountID",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Public",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Register",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api"]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } },
              "raw": "{\n  \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\n  \"method\": \"UserRegistrationService.Register\",\n  \"params\": [\n    {\n      \"email\": \"{{email}}\",\n      \"password\": \"{{password}}\",\n      \"name\": \"{{name}}\",\n      \"accountName\": \"{{accountName}}\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"id\": 1\n}"
            },
            "description": "Public. Creates a user and opens their first wallet account atomically, returning an access token so the caller is logged in immediately."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('no JSON-RPC error', () => pm.expect(body.error, JSON.stringify(body.error)).to.be.undefined);",
                  "if (body.result) {",
                  "  if (body.result.token)     { pm.collectionVariables.set('token', body.result.token); }",
                  "  if (body.result.userID)    { pm.collectionVariables.set('userID', body.result.userID); }",
                  "  if (body.result.accountID) { pm.collectionVariables.set('accountID', body.result.accountID); }",
                  "  console.log('captured token, userID and accountID from register');",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Login",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api"]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } },
              "raw": "{\n  \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\n  \"method\": \"EmailPasswordAuthenticator.Login\",\n  \"params\": [\n    {\n      \"email\": \"{{email}}\",\n      \"password\": \"{{password}}\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"id\": 1\n}"
            },
            "description": "Public. Authenticates with email and password and returns an access token. The test script stores result.token into the {{token}} collection variable."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('no JSON-RPC error', () => pm.expect(body.error, JSON.stringify(body.error)).to.be.undefined);",
                  "pm.test('token returned', () => pm.expect(body.result.token).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty);",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('token', body.result.token);",
                  "console.log('token captured into {{token}}');"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Protected",
      "description": "These require a valid token and a role permitted to call the method (RBAC enforced by the authorization middleware). Run Login first to populate {{token}}.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Wallet.ProcessTransaction",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{token}}", "type": "string" }]
            },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api"]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } },
              "raw": "{\n  \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\n  \"method\": \"Wallet.ProcessTransaction\",\n  \"params\": [\n    {\n      \"ref\": \"tx-1\",\n      \"account_id\": \"{{accountID}}\",\n      \"kind\": \"earn\",\n      \"points\": 100\n    }\n  ],\n  \"id\": 1\n}"
            },
            "description": "Records a single transaction. Callable by a member on an account they own (the server takes the actor from the token and enforces ownership; admins may act on any account). occurred_at is OPTIONAL — omit it (as here) and the server stamps it at processing time; supply an RFC 3339 value to back-date a transaction. Sends Authorization: Bearer {{token}}."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Wallet.ProcessTransactionBatch (admin-only)",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{token}}", "type": "string" }]
            },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api"]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } },
              "raw": "{\n  \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\n  \"method\": \"Wallet.ProcessTransactionBatch\",\n  \"params\": [\n    {\n      \"transactions\": [\n        {\n          \"ref\": \"batch-tx-1\",\n          \"account_id\": \"{{accountID}}\",\n          \"kind\": \"earn\",\n          \"points\": 100,\n          \"occurred_at\": \"2026-06-01T10:00:00Z\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"ref\": \"batch-tx-2\",\n          \"account_id\": \"{{accountID}}\",\n          \"kind\": \"spend\",\n          \"points\": 40,\n          \"occurred_at\": \"2026-06-01T11:00:00Z\"\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"id\": 1\n}"
            },
            "description": "ADMIN-ONLY. Applies an ordered batch of transactions in a single request. The server processes them strictly in array order (so the overdraft floor sees them in chronology — the CLI sorts by occurred_at before sending). Each element is its own unit of work: a rejected element does not roll back earlier accepted ones, and a repeated ref is reported as a duplicate. Returns { result: { results: [...], summary: { accepted, duplicate, rejected } } }. per-row occurred_at is optional, same as the single method. A member token is rejected with 'forbidden: batch ingestion is admin-only'."
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
